-- Matolcsy `Doesn't Deny' Hungarian Plan to Cut 10% of State Jobs, MTI Says
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2010-10-22T10:04:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/matolcsy-doesn-t-deny-hungarian-plan-to-cut-10-of-state-jobs-mti-says.html
Hungarian Economy Minister  Gyorgy Matolcsy  “didn’t deny” that the government is planning to cut
10 percent of public-sector jobs and reduce spending on state
bureaucracy by 5 percent,  MTI  news service reported today.  Matolcsy was responding to a statement from  Laszlo Varga ,
president of the Cooperative Forum of Labor Unions, during a
meeting today in Budapest with the heads of employer
associations and labor unions, MTI said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Zoltan Simon  in Budapest at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  